Alastair Cook confident England will recover
Captain Alastair Cook says he is "very confident" England's character and spirit will help them bounce back from their openingone-day international defeat by India.Cook admits his side were "out-skilled" by India, who now lead 1-0 in the five-match series, and says his side must now re-group in time for the second ODI in Delhi on Monday.Listen to commentary of India versus England on BBC Radio 5 live Sports Extra from 0945 on Monday 17 October.